      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0401P0-04252'>
        <a name='S6CV0401P0_20030311_WH_32'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-mark-francois' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0401P0_20030311_WH_32' title='Link to this speech by Mr Mark Francois' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-mark-francois" title="Mr Mark Francois">Mr. Francois</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            I entirely agree with my hon. Friend. As he pointed out, many women are very reliant on that
            
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_13wh' title='Col. 13WH &mdash; HC Deb 11 March 2003 vol 401 c13WH' name='column_13wh' href='#column_13wh' rel='bookmark'>13WH</a>
            type of pension and took reasonably rational decisions to invest in them some years ago when the stock market appeared to be performing in a particular way and, crucially, against a certain set of taxation rules. Those have now, in effect, been altered by the Chancellor with his grab raid.
